│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                              │
│                                                                          │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                          │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                              │
│ The crash occurs due to an assertion failure in                          │
│ InstructionsState::getMainOp() which requires InstructionsState to be    │
│ valid (i.e., both MainOp and AltOp must be non-null). The backtrace      │
│ shows that this happens inside BoUpSLP::getLastInstructionInBundle(),    │
│ which unconditionally calls E->getMainOp() for a TreeEntry.              │
│                                                                          │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                  │
│ The debug log indicates that the SLP builds several TreeEntries for      │
│ loads and proceeds to calculate costs for a reduction. The actual        │
│ assertion triggers during a path that analyzes gather shuffles           │
│ (processBuildVector -> isGatherShuffledEntry ->                          │
│ getLastInstructionInBundle). The getLastInstructionInBundle uses         │
│ E->getMainOp() to determine insertion points and ordering assumptions    │
│ about instructions in the bundle.                                        │
│                                                                          │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                  │
│ The codebase contains a special-case path in buildTreeRec that creates a │
│ gather TreeEntry with an invalid InstructionsState specifically when VL  │
│ contains only constants and PHI nodes:                                   │
│   if (AreOnlyConstsWithPHIs(VL)) { newGatherTreeEntry(VL,                │
│ InstructionsState::invalid(), UserTreeIdx); }                            │
│ This constructs a TreeEntry where S.valid() is false. Later routines     │
│ (like getLastInstructionInBundle and other cost estimators) assume the   │
│ TreeEntry has a valid InstructionsState and call getMainOp(), leading to │
│ the assertion.                                                           │
│ Even if the provided reproducer function contains only loads/xors, the   │
│ vectorizer often builds auxiliary gather nodes for constants/PHIs during │
│ horizontal reduction or operand collection. Any such node with invalid   │
│ InstructionsState will trigger this crash when routines expect a valid   │
│ MainOp.                                                                  │
│                                                                          │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                               │
│ Modify the branch that handles AreOnlyConstsWithPHIs(VL) in buildTreeRec │
│ to avoid creating TreeEntries with invalid InstructionsState. Select a   │
│ valid Instruction from VL (prefer a PHI if present) to serve as both     │
│ MainOp and AltOp; if no instruction exists (i.e., VL is all constants),  │
│ skip creating the entry to avoid downstream code accessing getMainOp()   │
│ on an invalid state.                                                     │
│                                                                          │
│ Edit at llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp lines            │
│ 10638-10641:                                                             │
│ - Current code:                                                          │
│   if (AreOnlyConstsWithPHIs(VL)) {                                       │
│     LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Gathering due to all constants and        │
│ PHIs.\n");                                                               │
│     newGatherTreeEntry(VL, InstructionsState::invalid(), UserTreeIdx);   │
│     return;                                                              │
│   }                                                                      │
│                                                                          │
│ - Replace with:                                                          │
│   if (AreOnlyConstsWithPHIs(VL)) {                                       │
│     LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "SLP: Gathering due to all constants and        │
│ PHIs.\n");                                                               │
│     // Ensure a valid InstructionsState: pick a PHI (or any instruction) │
│ if available.                                                            │
│     Instruction *MainAlt = nullptr;                                      │
│     for (Value *V : VL) {                                                │
│       if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) { MainAlt = I; break; }    │
│     }                                                                    │
│     if (MainAlt) {                                                       │
│       newGatherTreeEntry(VL, InstructionsState(MainAlt, MainAlt),        │
│ UserTreeIdx);                                                            │
│     } else {                                                             │
│       // VL contains only constants; skip creating an entry with invalid │
│ state.                                                                   │
│       // Constants will be materialized without scheduling; no tree      │
│ entry needed.                                                            │
│       return;                                                            │
│     }                                                                    │
│     return;                                                              │
│   }                                                                      │
│                                                                          │
│ This ensures that any TreeEntry created has a valid InstructionsState,   │
│ preventing getMainOp() assertions. For pure-constant vectors, skipping   │
│ the entry avoids introducing invalid states that later code would        │
│ traverse.                                                                │
│                                                                          │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                           │
│ By guaranteeing that newGatherTreeEntry is never called with             │
│ InstructionsState::invalid() in the constants/PHIs path, we prevent the  │
│ downstream assumption violation and assertion in getMainOp(). The fix    │
│ preserves existing behavior for PHI-containing bundles (providing a      │
│ valid representative instruction for scheduling/insertion point          │
│ determination) and safely avoids creating problematic entries for        │
│ all-constant bundles. This should eliminate the crash observed in the    │
│ reproducer and similar cases during horizontal reduction or gather       │
│ shuffle analysis.                                                        │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                          │
