  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash occurs due to an
assertion failure in InstructionsState::getMainOp() which requires
InstructionsState to be valid (i.e., both MainOp and AltOp must be
non-null). The backtrace shows that this happens inside
BoUpSLP::getLastInstructionInBundle(), which unconditionally calls
E->getMainOp() for a TreeEntry.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe debug log
indicates that the SLP builds several TreeEntries for loads and proceeds to
calculate costs for a reduction. The actual assertion triggers during a path
that analyzes gather shuffles (processBuildVector -> isGatherShuffledEntry
-> getLastInstructionInBundle). The getLastInstructionInBundle uses
E->getMainOp() to determine insertion points and ordering assumptions about
instructions in the bundle.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nThe codebase
contains a special-case path in buildTreeRec that creates a gather TreeEntry
with an invalid InstructionsState specifically when VL contains only
constants and PHI nodes:\n  if (AreOnlyConstsWithPHIs(VL)) {
newGatherTreeEntry(VL, InstructionsState::invalid(), UserTreeIdx); }\nThis
constructs a TreeEntry where S.valid() is false. Later routines (like
getLastInstructionInBundle and other cost estimators) assume the TreeEntry
has a valid InstructionsState and call getMainOp(), leading to the
assertion.\nEven if the provided reproducer function contains only
loads/xors, the vectorizer often builds auxiliary gather nodes for
constants/PHIs during horizontal reduction or operand collection. Any such
node with invalid InstructionsState will trigger this crash when routines
expect a valid MainOp.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\nModify the branch that
handles AreOnlyConstsWithPHIs(VL) in buildTreeRec to avoid creating
TreeEntries with invalid InstructionsState. Select a valid Instruction from
VL (prefer a PHI if present) to serve as both MainOp and AltOp; if no
instruction exists (i.e., VL is all constants), skip creating the entry to
avoid downstream code accessing getMainOp() on an invalid state.\n\nEdit at
llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp lines 10638-10641:\n-
Current code:\n  if (AreOnlyConstsWithPHIs(VL)) {\n    LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() <<
\"SLP: Gathering due to all constants and PHIs.\\n\");\n
newGatherTreeEntry(VL, InstructionsState::invalid(), UserTreeIdx);\n
return;\n  }\n\n- Replace with:\n  if (AreOnlyConstsWithPHIs(VL)) {\n
LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << \"SLP: Gathering due to all constants and
PHIs.\\n\");\n    // Ensure a valid InstructionsState: pick a PHI (or any
instruction) if available.\n    Instruction *MainAlt = nullptr;\n    for
(Value *V : VL) {\n      if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) { MainAlt =
I; break; }\n    }\n    if (MainAlt) {\n      newGatherTreeEntry(VL,
InstructionsState(MainAlt, MainAlt), UserTreeIdx);\n    } else {\n      //
VL contains only constants; skip creating an entry with invalid state.\n
// Constants will be materialized without scheduling; no tree entry
needed.\n      return;\n    }\n    return;\n  }\n\nThis ensures that any
TreeEntry created has a valid InstructionsState, preventing getMainOp()
assertions. For pure-constant vectors, skipping the entry avoids introducing
invalid states that later code would traverse.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nBy
guaranteeing that newGatherTreeEntry is never called with
InstructionsState::invalid() in the constants/PHIs path, we prevent the
downstream assumption violation and assertion in getMainOp(). The fix
preserves existing behavior for PHI-containing bundles (providing a valid
representative instruction for scheduling/insertion point determination) and
safely avoids creating problematic entries for all-constant bundles. This
should eliminate the crash observed in the reproducer and similar cases
during horizontal reduction or gather shuffle analysis.",
